{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow Visa applicants to pay health surcharge in instalments ",
        "additional_details": "We think requiring applicants to pay upfront often results in a surge of fee waiver applications, creating backlogs, delaying visa processing, and increasing taxpayer costs. We believe some applicants exploit this system to extend their stay while transitioning to another visa. We think the high upfront cost, especially for families, leads to frequent fee waiver approvals, causing financial losses for the government. We think instalment payments could curb fee waiver abuse, ease the Home Office\u2019s workload, and boost revenue.",
        "background": "If someone applies for a five-year visa, they currently must pay \u00a31,035 per year upfront, totalling \u00a35,175. We think applicants should have the option to pay the Immigration Health Surcharge in instalments instead of the full amount upfront for the entire visa duration.",
